title: Accounts Musk recommended on X belong to a teenager and a U.S. soldier
description: One social media account recommended by Elon Musk for coverage of the Israeli war with Hamas appears to be run by a London teenager, another by a U.S. soldier.

title: Tech execs fear future with AI: ‘I don’t know where optimism would spring from’
description: Despite long-awaited federal action anticipated next week, executives speaking Thursday at a Washington Post Live event said they were fearful of what a future with AI would bring.

title: White House backs up U.K. decision to invite China to AI summit
description: President Biden’s top science advisor on Thursday expressed support for the United Kingdom’s decision to invite China to its AI summit.

title: Schumer says ‘only real answer’ on AI is congressional action
description: Senate Majority Leader Charles E. Schumer (D-N.Y.) said an expected executive order from President Biden to deal with AI alone will not be enough.

title: From mommy bloggers to TikTok stars: How creators built a $250B industry
description: A brief history of the rise of the lucrative creator economy.

title: How creators became an economic juggernaut and the new American Dream
description: Millions of Americans have ditched traditional jobs to join the creator economy. In official records, they barely exist.

title: Candidates, take this AI election pledge. Or 2024 might break us.
description: The first AI election is here. Our tech columnist proposes some ground rules for candidates’ use of artificial intelligence.
